    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This one is useful as well when you want to implement a functional interface</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Runnable r = ()-&gt; System.out.print(&quot;Run method&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n<p>is equivalent to</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Runnable r = new Runnable() {\n        @Override\n        public void run() {\n            System.out.print(&quot;Run method&quot;);\n        }\n};\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9135339,
      "reputation" : 765,
      "user_id" : 6795222,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/66b581bb2a12c6810bdc29623ef78089?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Manasi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6795222/manasi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1556806217,
    "last_edit_date" : 1556806217,
    "creation_date" : 1553501881,
    "answer_id" : 55333644,
    "question_id" : 15146052,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>New Operator <strong>for lambda expression added in java 8</strong><BR></p>\n\n<p>Lambda expression is the <strong>short way of method writing.</strong><BR> \nIt is indirectly used to implement <a href=\"https://stacktraceguru.com/java-8-functional-interface?utm_source=stackoverflow&amp;utm_medium=post\" rel=\"noreferrer\">functional interface</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Primary Syntax : (parameters) -> { statements; }</strong></p>\n\n<p>There are some basic <a href=\"https://stacktraceguru.com/java-lambda-expression?utm_source=stackoverflow&amp;utm_medium=post#thinksToKnowAboutLambda\" rel=\"noreferrer\">rules for effective lambda expressions writting</a> which you should konw.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26995867,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 20557983,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/UvNA3.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "hiro hamanda",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/20557983/hiro-hamanda"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1669975740,
    "creation_date" : 1669975740,
    "answer_id" : 74654009,
    "question_id" : 15146052,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The arrow operator is used to create lambda expressions, linking/separating parameters with the lambda body.\nsyntax: (parameters) -&gt; {expression};\nIt is also an efficient way of implementing functional interfaces like onClickListeners in java.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 436296,
      "reputation" : 3092,
      "user_id" : 823368,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/jYVAT.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Andreas Panagiotidis",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/823368/andreas-panagiotidis"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1714211772,
    "creation_date" : 1714211772,
    "answer_id" : 78394581,
    "question_id" : 15146052,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just an example that works</p>\n<pre><code>interface StringFunction {  \n  String run(String strS, String strT);\n}\n\npublic class Main {\n  public static void main(String[] args) {  \n    \n    //Implement a function \n    StringFunction concatWithDotsFunction = (s , t) -&gt; s + &quot;...&quot; + t;\n    \n    String concatWithDotsResult = concatWithDotsFunction.run(&quot;Hello&quot; , &quot;you&quot;);\n    System.out.println(&quot;concatWithDotsResult: &quot; + concatWithDotsResult);\n        \n  \n    //Implement a function \n    StringFunction concatWithUnderscoreFunction = (s , t) -&gt; s + &quot; _ &quot; + t;\n    \n    //Call a method that takes the function as argument\n    printFormatted(&quot;Hello&quot;, &quot;you&quot; , concatWithUnderscoreFunction);\n        \n  }\n  \n  \n  public static void printFormatted(String strS, String strT, StringFunction function) {\n    String result = function.run(strS, strT);\n    \n    System.out.println(&quot;result: &quot; + result);    \n  }\n  \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
